The paper focuses on developing a new recurrent unit architecture for on-device low power acoustic event detection, which falls under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the efficiency and optimization of the architecture, which relates to machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of the architecture in wearable devices and IoT devices also relates to embedded systems (cs.ET). Finally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
